## Filter Galleries

All images are stored in a shared `_images/` folder. Galleries use filter expressions to select which images to display.

```
source/
â”œâ”€â”€ _index.revela          # Homepage
â”œâ”€â”€ _images/               # Shared image pool
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ canon-event-001.jpg
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ sony-landscape-002.jpg
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ sony-portrait-003.jpg
â”œâ”€â”€ canon/
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ _index.revela      # filter = "exif.make == 'Canon'"
â”œâ”€â”€ sony/
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ _index.revela      # filter = "exif.make == 'Sony'"
â””â”€â”€ portraits/
    â””â”€â”€ _index.revela      # filter = "contains(filename, 'portrait')"
```

### The `_images/` Folder

The underscore prefix is significant:

- `_images/` is **not** rendered as a gallery itself
- Images are only accessible via filter expressions
- You can use any name: `_photos/`, `_pool/`, `_shared/`

### Example Front Matter

```toml
+++
title = "Canon Photos"
description = "All photos taken with Canon cameras"
filter = "exif.make == 'Canon'"
+++
```

